  AUTO_LEVELS: On
  NODE_IN_TOC: True

[[SECTION]]
TITLE: 1. Purpose

[TEXT]
STATEMENT: >>>
Parent file for GHOST interfaces. Defines current/future UI boundary, Streamlit as current implemented workbench, React/TypeScript and FastAPI as future interface architecture, UI ownership rules, separation between UI rendering and subsystem logic, and UI surfaces.
<<<

[[/SECTION]]

[[SECTION]]
TITLE: 2. Scope and Boundary

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-UI-ROOT
TITLE: GHOST Human Workbench and Interface Scope
STATEMENT: >>>
This file is a draft child requirement file in the GHOST StrictDoc requirement tree.

It defines ownership, scope, and placeholder headings for this capability area. Detailed atomic requirements shall be migrated here from legacy requirements, implementation status, architecture notes, UML files, and code evidence after human approval.

This file shall not duplicate detailed requirements owned by sibling files.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-SRS-FILE-TREE

